{
  "texts": [
    "It is this combination of GS-type variables for AdS 3 × S 3 and (topologically-twisted) RNS-like variables for T 4 from which the name \"hybrid\" is derived.Following [12,40] and working at generic k ∈ N, there is a (small) N = 4 topological algebra in the string theory generated byT = T W ZW + T σ + T ρ + T C, G -= e -iσ + G - C, G + = -e -2ρ-iσ P + e -ρ Q + e iσ T + G + C, G+ = e ρ+iH + e ρ+iσ G+ C, G-= -e -3ρ-2iσ-iH P + e -2ρ-iσ-iH Q -e -ρ-iH T -e -ρ-iσ G- C, J = 1 2 ∂(ρ + iσ) + J C, J ±± = e ±ρ±iσ±iH,(2.10)wherefoot_6 T = T W ZW - 1 2 (∂(ρ + iσ)) 2 + 1 2 ∂ 2 (ρ + iσ).The operator T W ZW is the Sugawara energy momentum tensor associated to the WZW model for psu(1, 1|2) k and similarly P and Q depend only on the WZW variables.",
    "Q is weight three, depending on both the supercharges and the bosonic currents, whilst P is quartic in the supercharges but independent of the bosonic currents.",
    "The operators containing a subscript C correspond to the N = 4 topological algebra of the compact T 4.",
    "We use the conventions of [10] for these operators,T C = ∂X j ∂ Xj -λj ∂λ j, G - C = λj ∂X j, G- C = ϵ ij λi ∂ Xj, J -- C = -λ1 λ2, G + C = λ j ∂ Xj, G+ C = ϵ ij λ i ∂X j, J C = 1 2 λ j λj, J ++ C = λ 1 λ 2, (2.11) JHEP04(2024)048where j ∈ {1, 2} and ϵ 12 = +1.",
    "The topological twisting means that (∂X j, ∂ Xj) are complex bosons, each of weight (1, 0), whilst λ j and λj are complex fermions of weights (0, 0) and (1, 0) respectively."
  ]
}